Paris Saint-Germain forward, Kylian Mbappé on Sunday scored a brace in his side’s Ligue 1 4-0 victory over 10-man St Etienne. The France international helped his side to extend their lead on the table with seven points ahead of second place, Marseille. However, Leandro Paredes and Mauro Icardi did score a goal each for PSG against the host. The victory over St Etienne means PSG are now on top of the Ligue 1 table with 42 points from 17 games. PSG will take on Amiens in their next Ligue 1 fixture on December 21. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.